    "actor_description": "It hits hot and stupid-my stomach tightens, my chest goes hard, and my attention keeps snapping back no matter what I tell myself. I watch and compare without meaning to, and the comparison feels like losing. I want to look indifferent. I can't. There's this embarrassing urgency under my skin: the urge to reclaim space, to matter more, to be the obvious choice. The worst part is the self-awareness of it-how small it makes me feel-while the feeling keeps burning anyway.",
    "description_text": "{actor} grows visibly unsettled: their gaze keeps returning in sharp, involuntary flicks, then darting away as if caught. Color rises in the face; the jaw tightens. They hover between reaching and retreating-half-steps forward that stop short, gestures aborted mid-motion.",
